description:
Responsibilities
Reporting to the Officer (Licensing), the appointee will be required to:
Conduct data entry and update information for licence applications;
Scan, maintain and file the application documents;
Provide clerical support to the licensing application process and produce periodic statistical reports;
Liaise and follow up with respective applicants on licence application when necessary;
Undertake ad-hoc tasks as assigned from time to time.
Requirements
Tertiary education or above in any disciplines;
A minimum of 1 year relevant experience;
Relevant work experience and knowledge in processing data and report generation are preferable;
Independent and able to work under pressure;
Knowledge in MS Word and Excel is a must;
Good command in Chinese and English input; and
Immediately available is highly preferable.
* Contract Period: Jan – End of March 2022

Terms of Appointment
Remuneration will be commensurate with qualifications and experience. A temporary contract will be offered to the successful candidate. The PMSA is an equal opportunity employer and welcomes applications from all qualified candidates.
Application Procedure
Interested applicants may send a full curriculum vitae indicating current and expected salaries to General Manager (Operation and Service), The Property Management Services Authority, Units 806-8, 8/F, Dah Sing Financial Centre, 248 Queen’s Road East, Wan Chai, Hong Kong or by email. Please mark “PRIVATE & CONFIDENTIAL”, the position applied for and the reference number on the envelope.
The closing date for application is 31 January 2022.  Recruitment will continue until the position is filled. Applicants not invited for interview within 6 weeks from the date of application may consider their application unsuccessful.
All applications will be treated in strict confidence. Personal data provided will only be used for job application processing.

Key Responsibilities:


Support the development and operation of talent development programmes by working with both internal departments and external partners including training service providers, NGOs and higher education institutions;
Plan, coordinate and organise events and training workshops for education & the talent development programmes;
Take part in different events, projects or initiatives to facilitate community companies in recruiting and engaging talents;
Drive business collaboration to catalyze the expansion of partner companies; and
Perform any other duties as assigned by supervisors or management.

Requirements:



University graduate in Business, Science, Engineering or related discipline.
Minimum 6 years of relevant work experience in education / learning programme development and operation, preferably in STEM related discipline at tertiary education level;
Experience in handling funding programmes, academic institutions and NGOs;
Good understanding of working with college / university students is preferred;
Proactive team player with excellent problem-solving skills, pleasant and outgoing with excellent communication and interpersonal management skills across the Corporation and with outside partners as well as enthusiastic about working with students;
Proactive team player with excellent problem-solving skills, pleasant and outgoing with excellent communication and interpersonal management skills across the Corporation and with outside partners as well as enthusiastic about working with students;
Proficiency in both spoken and written English and Chinese (including Putonghua)
The position is on a renewable 2-year fixed-term contract, subject to performance and operational needs, the position will convert into open contract after 2 years.


We offer competitive package to the right candidate. Interested party please click Apply Now to apply on or before 11 February 2022 in confidence with full resume in Word document, stating present and expected salary, and available date and quote the reference. 

Applicants who do not hear from us by 25 February 2022 may assume that their applications are unsuccessful.

Further information about the Cyberport is available at http://www.cyberport.hk

You will be responsible for:
formulating and co-ordinating the business strategy, direction and plans for car park operations in West Kowloon Cultural District (WKCD);
managing third party car park operators engaged in WKCD and overseeing their day-to-day operations to ensure compliance with the Authority’s standards, requirements and procedures;
monitoring financial performance of third party car park operators and identifying opportunities for enhancing revenue generated for West Kowloon Cultural District Authority (WKCDA) through promotions, fee adjustments, cross-district initiatives etc;
reviewing service contracts related to the operation of car parks in WKCD and regularly monitor for quality and performance;
overseeing facilities and equipment required for operating WKCD car parks and the responsible party for implementing/maintaining such infrastructure;
developing improvement plans for standard procedures, control measures and environmentally friendly measures related to the parking operation in WKCD including opportunities for enhancing the overall parking visitor experience in WKCD;
advising and co-ordinating with other Departments on future planned car parking areas in WKCD from initial design through to operation;
managing all maintenance and repair contracts for car parking areas to ensure compliance with maintenance standards; and
co-ordinating with other teams to arrange cleaning, repair and maintenance work for car parking areas in WKCDA.
You should:
possess a recognized university degree/ tertiary education in real estate, business management or related disciplines;
have at least 10 years of experience in carpark and facilities management, operation and development; exposure to the arts and cultural environment or tourism sector will be an advantage; 
have solid supervisory skills and experience in managing local sizable car parks;
possess knowledge of latest car park management systems and technology; and
have strong interpersonal skills and be proficient in written and spoken communication skills in English and Chinese.
For interested parties, please submit your application with detailed CV on or before 25 January 2022. Applicants are encouraged to submit their applications as soon as possible.  The review of applications will continue until the post is filled.
Data collected will only be used for job application processing. Your data may be accessed by our appointed recruitment consultants who have agreed to keep confidence of all personal data in not less than the standards applicable to us. Applicants not being invited for interview within 4 weeks from the submission date may assume their applications unsuccessful.
All related information will be kept up to 24 months and all personal data will be destroyed afterwards.
For more information
http://www.westkowloon.hk or contact
Ms. Amanda Tai at 2200-0116

Responsibilities
Reporting to the Manager (Administration & Resources Management), the appointee will be required to:
Provide administrative and clerical support to the PMSA Executive Office;
Perform offsite duties such as mailing, documents/parcel collection and delivery and cheques bank-in, etc., when necessary;
Assist in organising and coordinating arrangements for meetings and corporate events/activities; and
Undertake ad-hoc tasks as assigned from time to time.

Requirements

Tertiary education or above, preferably in Business Administration;
1-2 years of relevant working experience;
Fresh graduates will also be considered;
Proficiency in Microsoft Office applications including Word, Excel, PowerPoint and Chinese Word Processing;
A good team player with strong sense of responsibility, good interpersonal and problem solving skills;
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese;
Immediate availability is highly preferred.
Terms of Appointment
Remuneration will be commensurate with qualifications and experience. A 1-month contract will be offered to the successful candidate. The PMSA is an equal opportunity employer and welcomes applications from all qualified candidates.
Application Procedure
Interested applicants should send a full curriculum vitae indicating current and expected salaries to General Manager (Operation and Service), The Property Management Services Authority, Units 806-8, 8/F, Dah Sing Financial Centre, 248 Queen’s Road East, Wan Chai, Hong Kong or by email. Please mark “PRIVATE & CONFIDENTIAL”, the position applied for and the reference number on the envelope.

The closing date for application is 13 January 2022.  Recruitment will continue until the position is filled. Applicants not invited for interview within 6 weeks from the date of application may consider their application unsuccessful.

All applications will be treated in strict confidence. Personal data provided will only be used for job application processing.
